		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Bruce Holland Rogers</span></strong> leaves this month for Japan, where he plans to walk the Tōkaidō Road between Tokyo and Kyoto, visiting the fifty-three stations, or overnight stopping points, that were the inspiration for Ando Hiroshige&rsquo;s nineteenth-century woodblock prints.</p><a href="/contributors/bruce-holland-rogers" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
